				<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0>
				posted 2005-01-28 00:49&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=15908"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=15610"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Some basic things:<br />
<br />
1) Invest immediately in research, and planet, with a tiny bit into ships (I usually go 25k research, 20k into planet, and 5k into pool). Also, It might be a good idea to change the % on your home planet....I personnaly go pretty much 60% fact, 10% research, 30% bases...<br />
2) Recall your fleet from your home planet.<br />
3) Reassign one of your fleets (fleet 1 or 2 I think...the one with shittier empire designed fleets) to only 5 ships<br />
4) Form a new fleet with the ship you just took out of your crappy fleet<br />
5) send the 1 ship fleet to expedition<br />
6) Go and design a cruiser with the best weapon you have (probably fussion)<br />
7) cue to build a pile of cruisers<br />
8) When you get planets, set them to ~10% fact, 80% research, 10% miliatry, UNLESS they are rich or UR, in which case they go 100% factory, and adjust some of your other planets to less factory and more research to make up for it<br />
9) log on fairly often in the first few days to make sure you have money invested in everything as much as possible<br />
<br />
That should be good enough to get most people started, although I am sure some of the vets who finish near the top each set and tech quickly have slightly different strategy....just make sure that you design better fleets as they become available, and that you don't declare war on anyone who you cannot beat down in your council, or who is still in protection, since they will come out of it when you may be offline and you may get killed :)<br />
<br />
Houston<br />
Canadian Right<br />
<br />
PS, to test if someone is in your cluster, or in protection, try blockading them with a gunboat before you declare war...if they are not in your cluster, or are in protection, then it will tell you that as you go to attack)			   <P align=right></P>
